rComments: Great professor! She keeps things interesting and lively. Took it as an elective, now seriously thinking of changing my career path.
Really great prof.  Knows the material and uses lots of personal examples to demonstrate the theory.  Beware her marking on the group project.
By far the BEST Professor at the University of Toronto. She takes the time to teach her students - her lectures are incredibly engaging. One of a kind, an absolute treasure!!!
Took "Leadership" with Prof. Shantz. Amazing, engaged professor. Well prepared; interesting lectures and assignments. Learned a lot.  Highly recommend taking her class!!
Great professor, very helpful and approachable
Absolutely the best prof I've ever had!  It's rare to find an educator of higher learning who truly cares about her/his students, but she really does.

She makes learning a true pleasure with her energy and constant pursuit of learning through the exchanging of ideas. Her teaching approach from separating self efficacy/self esteem to constant efforts to make student's appreciate the material is infectious.
Best professor at u of t.  Had her as a TA for OB and as a professor for MGT 460.  Highly approachable, does not intimidate students, genuinely cares about her students.  Interesting lectures.
